(1) Port
---------
==> sets or returns the port number the server uses for a URL

==> If the port number is not specified in the URL (or if it is the scheme's default port - like 80, or 443), some browsers will display 0 or nothing

EX: Get Port Of (localhost:3000)
-----

	window.location.port  // "3000"
	
	Or
	
	location.port // "3000"
	
	
EX: Set Port To 5000
-----

	window.location.port = "5000" // http://localhost:5000/ 
	window.location.port = 5000 // http://localhost:5000/ 
	
	Or
	
	location.port = "5000" // http://localhost:5000/
	location.port = 5000 // http://localhost:5000/
